## Traps

- `pytest --timeout-method=signal` hangs on asyncio selector loops;
  use `--timeout-method=thread`.
- Worktree dispatches silently base on old commits. Before cherry-
  picking any `worktree-agent-*` branch, check `git merge-base
  <branch> main`. Prefer wholesale file-checkout if diverged too
  far (see commit `911722aa` pattern).
- `PostToolUse` formatter sometimes reverts Edits; re-apply sticks.
- Pre-commit hook `pytest-check` resolves to worktree-absolute paths
  and fails in isolated worktrees. Use `git -c core.hooksPath=
  /dev/null commit` with bypass documented in commit body per
  `rules/git.md`.
- `git checkout <branch> -- <path>` run from inside an agent
  worktree operates on the worktree's tree, not `main`. Always
  verify `git branch --show-current` before applying cross-worktree
  ops.
- SQLite `UpdateNode` / `UpsertNode` return metadata (filter,
  fields, rows_affected), NOT the row. PostgreSQL returns the row
  via RETURNING. Always read-back if you need the full record.
